cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze eye-tracking data during reading. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a Fisher-SVM with a Fisher kernel, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely category. The paper also involves computer vision techniques to analyze eye movements, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper deals with human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of a generative model, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
